# Capitol Trades data source
> This dataset collects financial disclosure reports for Senators, former Senators current and former 
> members of the House filed from 2012 to present.

The Ethics in Government Act (EIGA, specifically 5 U.S.C. app. §§ 101-112), Senate Rule 34, and Senate Rule 41, 
require Members, officers, certain employees, and candidates to file public Financial Disclosure Reports with the 
Secretary of the Senate, Office of Public Records.    
The Committee administers the financial disclosure reporting program for the U.S. Senate.    

In addition, the Stop Trading on Congressional Knowledge Act (STOCK Act) requires the Senate to establish and 
maintain an electronic filing system for Financial Disclosure Reports.
 
Visit [senate.gov/financialdisclosure][4] or [disclosures-clerck.house.gov][5] for authoritative references

#### Change log (reverse historical order - most recent first)

v0.1-d    
  - Consistent use of Transaction over Trade on field names and descriptions 
  - Create FLD043, PricingSourcePrice field with the value of the price from the identified PCS 
  - Create FLD042, PricingSource field with the name of the data source where the price was fetched 
  - Update FLD019, PoliticalParty description 
  - Create FLD041, ISIN
  - Remove FLD029, SEDOL licensing restrictions
  - Create FLD040, CUSIP with the traded asset's cusip code

v0.1-c    
  - Update FLD007, TransactionType description with the allowed values for SELL transaction types
  - Create FLD039, IsPartialSell flag signaling that the sell transaction is only closing a partial position
  - Rename FLD038, IsPositionSquaring to FLD038, IsPositionClose  
  - Create FLD038, IsPositionSquaring flag signaling that the sell transaction is closing the whole position
  - Create FLD037, ValueRangeHigh with the high range of the traded value
  - Rename FLD013, ValueRange to FLD013 ValueRangeLow
  - Rename FLD012, ValueAverage to FLD012, Value
  - Rename FLD036, PriceRangeHigh with the high value of the range 
  - Create FLD035, SizeRangeHigh with the high value of the range 
  - Rename FLD008, SizeRangeLow from FLD008, SizeRange with the lower bound of the size range 
  - Create FLD034, RepresentedDistrict as a more specific level of FLD020, RepresentedState 
  - Create FLD033, OtherPartyName with the description of what the "Other" party in FLD019, PoliticalParty stands for  
  - Update FLD005, Owner allowed format 
  - Add source [5]
  - Rename FLD014, CustodianName to FLD014, TransactionComment

v0.1-b    
  - Rename a few other fields and consolidate numbering scheme    
  - Create FLD017, RowCreation the UTC timestamp of when the bot scrapped the data
  - Create FLD030, ISIN
  - Create FLD029, CUSIP
  - Rename FLD029 and FLD030 to FLD031 and FLD032  
  - Expand FLD015, CustodianName description
  - Rename FLD024, LinkedInProfile due to the lack of information to FLD024, Tenure 
  - Remove FLD021, EthnicityId due to the lack of detailed Ethnicity information
  - Change FLD011, CapitalGains type from money to boolean flag
  - Remove FDL013, ValueRangeMax
  - Rename FLD012, ValueRangeMin from ValueRangeMin to ValueRange  
  - Expand FLD010, Price description




