## Data delivery methods
(TODO: Ruven + Huzaifa + Muaz need to agree on what delivery methods will be available)

#### 1. Postgres database     
    hostname: some-server.some-domain.pk   
    database: data-collection   
    read-only credentials upon request

#### 2. API endpoint    
  There is a public API endpoint that can be queried using standard HTTP tools ([place-where-the-swagger-spec-is][3])    
  Please note that bot protection is in effect - the requests will be rate limited

#### 3. S3 bucket    
  A set of files is available for delivery into an S3 bucket upon request    
  There are two main sets of files: a snapshot file with the current view of the data, and, an incremental file with    
  changes as they happen over time.   

  Replaying the snapshot files will rebuild the snapshot.

  The standard bucket's structure:

    capitol_trades
      │
      ├─── datasource-info.yaml
      ├─── datasource-info.md
      ├─── incremental
      │       ├─── 20210731_170903-transaction.csv
      │       ├─── 20210731_170906-transaction.csv
      │       ├─── 20210731_170903-person.csv
      │       └─── 20210731_170906-person.csv
      ├─── snapshot
      │        ├─── 20210731_235959_transaction_snapshot.csv
      │        ├─── 20210730_235959_transaction_snapshot.csv
      │        ├─── 20210731_235959_person_snapshot.csv
      │        └─── 20210730_235959_person_snapshot.csv
      └─── readme.md


## Data delivery frequency
(TODO: Ruven + Huzaifa + Muaz need to agree on the delivery schedule)

New data is available three times a day on the following schedule: `HHMMSS`, `HHMMSS`, `HHMMSS`.  
The daily snapshot will be made available daily at 00:05:00 UTC including every transaction of the previous day.   

## Data coverage
Coverage for Senator and Former Senators transactions starts on `2012-07-09`  
Coverage for Representatives (see `FLD0004, ReportingIndividualId`) starts on `2012-07-25` 

## Point-In-Time approach
There is no point-in-time as of now - each snapshot file contains the entire "view of reality" up until the timestamp of the export.    
If you are looking to reproduce an individual's holdings over time, you need to iterate over all historical snapshots and rebuild it from there.

## Field specification
Catalog of all fields made available by the data source per type of entity

### Transaction
| Field ID 	| Field Name 	| Field Description 	|
|----------	|------------	|-------------------	|
|FLD001   	| TransactionId      	| Unique identifier for each transaction |
|FLD002   	| TransactionDate    	| Date the transaction settled |
|FLD003   	| PublicationDate | "Digital Signature Date" on the filing metadata |
|FLD017   	| RowCreation | Timestamp when the bot consumed the filing |
|FLD004   	| ReportingIndividualId | Identifier for the individual that reported the transaction |
|FLD005   	| Owner	        | Person who actually traded (see description) |
|FLD006   	| AssetID	    | Unique identifier of the asset that was traded |
|FLD007   	| TransactionType | The transaction type |
|FLD008   	| SizeRangeLow    | The low range of the size, in units, of the transaction (i.e.: number of shares traded) |
|FLD035   	| SizeRangeHigh   | The high range of the size, in units, of the transaction (i.e.: number of shares traded) |
|FLD009   	| Size   | The size, in units, of the transaction (i.e.: number of shares traded) |
|FLD010   	| Price         | The price, in USD, of the shares traded |
|FLD012   	| Value  | The traded value |
|FLD013   	| ValueRangeLow | The low bound of the value range for the transaction |
|FLD037   	| ValueRangeHigh | The high bound of the value range for the transaction |
|FLD011   	| HasCapitalGains  | Flag identifying if there were capital gains >$200 |
|FLD014   	| TransactionComment | A comment to the transaction |
|FLD015   	| FilingURL | The original filing URL |
|FLD016   	| FilingID | The opaque filingID from the original filing |
|FLD038   	| IsPositionClose | Identifying a close of the entire position |
|FLD039   	| IsPartialSell | Identifying a partial close of a larger position |
|FLD042   	| PricingSource | Pricing Source identification |
|FLD043   	| PricingSourcePrice | Pricing Source price |


### ReportingIndividual
| Field ID 	| Field Name 	| Field Description 	|
|----------	|------------	|-------------------	|
|FLD004   	| ReportingIndividualId | Identifier for the individual that reported the transaction |
|FLD019   	| PoliticalParty | The individual's political party |
|FLD033   	| OtherPartyName | The name of the political party represented in FLD019 |
|FLD020   	| RepresentedState | The State of the reporting individual |
|FLD021   	| PictureURL | URL of the individual's picture |
|FLD022   	| TwitterProfile | The Twitter handle of the reporting individual |
|FLD023   	| Tenure | The candidate's tenure |
|FLD034   	| RepresentedDistrict | The District of the reporting individual |


### Assets
| Field ID 	| Field Name 	| Field Description 	|
|----------	|------------	|-------------------	|
|FLD006   	| AssetID	    | Unique identifier of the asset that was traded |
|FLD026   	| AssetType	    | The asset type of the asset |
|FLD027   	| AssetName	    | A descriptive name of the asset |
|FLD028   	| Ticker	    | Bloomberg Ticker of the asset |
|FLD030   	| GVKey         | Compustat's GVKey identifier for the traded asset |
|FLD031   	| IID           | Compustat's IID identifier for the traded asset |
|FLD040   	| CUSIP         | CUSIP code of the traded asset |
|FLD041   	| ISIN          | ISIN code of the traded asset |



### Field specification
#### FLD001, TransactionId
> `Type:` number    
> `Unique:` yes    
> `Format:`     
> `Description` A unique number that identifies each transaction

#### FLD002, TransactionDate
> `Type:` date    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Format:` ISO8601 YYYY-MM-DD    
> `Description` An ISO8601 date of when the transaction settled

#### FLD003, PublicationDate
> `Type:` timestamp    
> `Unique:` no   
> `Format:` ISO8601 YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssZ000    
> `Description` An ISO8601 date of when the data was available in the eFD website
>  Maps to the "Digitally Signed Date" metadata field in the filing

#### FLD017, RowCreation
> `Type:` timestamp    
> `Unique:` no   
> `Format:` ISO8601 YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssZ000    
> `Description` An ISO8601 UTC date of when the data was scraped from the Senate's e-Financial Disclosures website 
> or from House of Representatives’ Disclosures Clerk website.  
> This is the date that should be used for analytics as this is the date when the 
> general public was made aware of the transaction and could act on that information.  
> Assume that the data collection process runs every 30 min - this is the max delay between a filing is publicly disclosed
> and the collection process ingests the new filing.

#### FLD004, ReportingIndividualId
> `Type:` number    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Description` A numeric identifier linking a `FLD004, ReportingIndividualId` to a transaction (see Person lookup table)  

#### FLD005, Owner
> `Type:` text     
> `Unique:` no    
> `Format:`  `Spouse`, `Not Disclosed`, `Child`, `Self`, `Joint`  
> `Description`     
>  A text field that contains the relationship type between the reporting member and the ultimate beneficiary of the transaction.     
>  In practice this can be someone (spouse, child, ...) that by House of Representatives' regulation is required to report a transaction    
>  Do not confuse this field with `FLD004, ReportingIndividualId` which represents the reporting individual

#### FLD006, AssetID
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Description`   
>  A text field identifying the traded asset ID    

#### FLD007, TransactionType
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Format:` BUY | SELL | EXCHANGED | RECEIVED    
> `Description`  
> A text field identifying the type of transaction    
>   - BUY - Increase the holdings of the asset  
>   - SELL - Decrease the holdings of the asset  
>   - EXCHANGED - Equivalent to "Security Transfer Out" in case of merger transactions   
>   - RECEIVED - Equivalent to "Security Transfer In" in case of merger transactions  
> 
> See `FLD038, IsPositionClose` and `FLD039, IsPartialSell` for additional information on the specific action.
> 
> According to the [Senate Guidelines][6] the concepts of a "Partial or Full" position sell don't exist - 
> those transaction are simply a SELL with no additional flags.          
> The [House of Representative Guidelines][7] details what a "Partial" sell is, but, makes no explicit mention 
> to a "Full" position close.

#### FLD008, SizeRangeLow
> `Type:` Number        
> `Unique:` no    
> `Format:` nnnnnnnn  
> `Description`  
>   A numeric  value specifying the low end of the range representation for the number of shares traded    
>   Examples: `15` for the range `15 - 221`     

#### FLD035, SizeRangeHigh
> `Type:` Number        
> `Unique:` no    
> `Format:` nnnnnnnn  
> `Description`  
>   A numeric  value specifying the high end of the range representation for the number of shares traded    
>   Examples: `221` for the range `15 - 221`     

#### FLD009, Size
> `Type:` Number    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Format:` nnnnnnnn  
> `Description`  
>   A numeric value representing the average number of shares traded (if a range was not supplied)    
>   Examples: `1,000`, `--`          

#### FLD010, Price
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Format:` "," is the thousands' separator, "." is the decimal separator    
> `Undefined value:` --       
> `Description`  
>  The price the transaction was executed, quoted in USD   
 
#### FLD012, Value
> `Type:` money    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Undefined value:` --       
> `Description` Total traded amount, quoted in USD    

#### FLD013, ValueRangeLow
> `Type:` money    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Undefined value:` --       
> `Description` Low end of the range of the traded amount, quoted in USD    
 
#### FLD037, ValueRangeHigh
> `Type:` money    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Undefined value:` --       
> `Description` High end of the range of the traded amount, quoted in USD    

#### FLD011, HasCapitalGains
> `Type:` boolean    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Undefined value:` --       
> `Description` True if the transaction returned capital gains  
> This field is only relevant for Representatives and only if a transaction resulted in a capital gain >$200, 
> Senators do not report this information

#### FLD014, TransactionComment
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Undefined value:` --       
> `Description` A text field with an additional comment about the specific transaction 

#### FLD015, FilingURL
> `Type:` url    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Format:` RFC 8820       
> `Description` e-Financial Disclosure's filling URL

#### FLD016, FilingID
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Description` e-Financial Disclosure's filling ID

#### FLD038, IsPositionClose
> `Type:` bool    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Description` A boolean flag indicating that the SELL transaction from `FLD007, TransactionType` is closing the 
> entire position

#### FLD039, IsPartialSell
> `Type:` bool    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Description` A boolean flag indicating that the SELL transaction from `FLD007, TransactionType` is only closing part 
> of a larger position.  
> Note that, according to the regulations, 

#### FLD042, PricingSource
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Format:` `Compustat` | `Binance` | `Kraken` | `...`    
> `Description`  
> The pricing source identification used to price the transaction

#### FLD043, PricingSourcePrice
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Format:` "," is the thousands' separator, "." is the decimal separator    
> `Undefined value:` --       
> `Description`  
>  The price at the pricing source, quoted in USD


### Person
The lookup table for individuals that are legally required to report (Senators, Representatives, ...)

#### FLD004, ReportingIndividualId
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` yes    
> `Description` The unique identifier of a reporting individual

#### FLD019, PoliticalParty
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Format:`  `Republican` | `Democrat` | `Independent` | `Independent Democrat` | `Libertarian` | `Other`  
> `Description` The political affiliation of the reporting person
> Typical values are:
>   - Republican  
>   - Democrat  
>   - Independent  
>   - Independent Democrat  
>   - Libertarian
>   - Other (See `FLD033, OtherPartyName`)

#### FLD033, OtherPartyName
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Description` A text field that extends `FLD019, PoliticalParty` and specifies what the "Other" party is

#### FLD020, RepresentedState
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Description` The state represented by the individual

#### FLD034, RepresentedDistrict
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` false    
> `Description` The reporting individual's represented district (see `FLD020, ReportingState`)  

#### FLD021, PictureURL
> `Type:` url    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Format:` RFC 8820        
> `Description` A url where the official photograph of the individual can be retrieved   

#### FLD022, TwitterProfile
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` true    
> `Description` The twitter handle of the individual 

#### FLD023, Tenure
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` false    
> `Description` The current tenure of the candidate (at the trade date)  
>   Examples: `House: 2017-Present`, `House: 2013-2015`     


### Asset
The lookup table for traded assets

#### FLD006, AssetID
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` yes     
> `Description`   
> The unique identifier of the traded asset

#### FLD026, AssetType
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no     
> `Description`   
> The text field with the name of the traded asset.
>   ABS -      
>   Corporate Bond -      
>   Crypto -     
>   ETF -      
>   Hedge / Pvt Eq Funds (non-EIF) -     
>   Municipal Security -     
>   Mutual Fund -     
>   Non-Public Stock -     
>   Other Securities -     
>   Ownership Interest -     
>   Stock -     
>   Stock Options -     

#### FLD027, AssetName
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Description`   
> The text field with the name of the traded asset

#### FLD028, Ticker
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Description`   
> A text field identifying the ticker of the traded asset

#### FLD030, GVKey
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Description`   
> A text field identifying the Compustat's GVKey code of the traded asset

#### FLD031, IID
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Description`   
> A text field identifying Compustat's IID code of the traded asset

#### FLD040, CUSIP
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Description`   
> A text field with the traded asset's CUSIP code

#### FLD041, ISIN
> `Type:` text    
> `Unique:` no    
> `Description`   
> A text field with the traded asset's ISIN code


